n, women, and children; the watershed moment of the invention of money; the collective action of workers; and at the impact of migration, slavery, and the idea of leisure. From peasant farmers in the first agrarian societies to the precarious existence of today’s gig workers, this surprising account of both cooperation and subordination at work throws essential light on the opportunities we face today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Sep 2021) 0aLaborxHistory. 0aWorkxHistory. 7aHISTORY / World.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300262995423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300262995/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles